          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is used for contemplation, study, and recitation, and is a poetic work and philosophical interpretation of devotional traditions associated with the Hindu deity Viṣṇu, defining three different kinds of devotees, prakṛtas, madhyamas, and mahābhaktas, representing lower and higher forms of worship respectively. Manuscript has an extensive commentary (vyākhyā) running parallel, above and below the main text.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
